Where content is removed from an FRX before the start of contextual content, an empty row is added to the table and removed from display.

This line doesn't accommodate the cell structure of the row and so makes the browser work out what to display. 
{code}<tr style="display: none;" class="diffStart" id="diffStart27107"><td> </td></tr>{code}

By adding in a colspan, the heavy calculations are done on the server and not in the browser
{code}<tr style="display: none;" class="diffStart" id="diffStart27107" colspan="7"><td> </td></tr>{code}

{quote}
Add grades to be assigned to a review along a set of user defined dimensions, (think like a 1-5 scale or something)? I.e. Architecture, Documentation, Testing, and Standards for instance.

What we want to do is to define say 4 or 5 dimensions that a code review is being rated on. So say for instance one would be adherence to coding standards another might be properly tested and yet another could be design/architectural cohesiveness. As part of the review we'd want to assign a grade on a scale from 1 to 5 along these dimensions that would get stored logged with the review and potentially the data would be available to report on.
{quote}

{quote}
As a reviewer, if I only wanted to see comments related to a specific revision selected using the revision node handles, how would I do that?

Right now I can see all the comments related to all the versions and can use Display preferences to hide, move above or show inline. I can hover over the comment to see which revision its assigned to but thats it.
{quote}
